to slim a bloated organisation.
Thai's load factor climbed to 69.2 per cent from 65.8 per cent. However, Mr
Thamnoon said that the six new aircraft due for delivery in the next
financial year would depress next year's load factors to about 68-69 per
cent.
Mr Luc Perron at brokers HG Asia said: 'This is a turnround - there's a
definite improvement in efficiency and a pick-up in traffic growth.'
